<br />

<br />
That was my idea originally I think. Essentially the ward would stack on top of the current DS line, like bard song does. Except that it would stack with bard song and other mage's wards also. The intent is to make a non-main buff window DS that would be useful both on raids and in groups. 
<br />

<br />
So on a raid with 3 mages you'd get something like:
<br />
Maelstrom of Ro (45)
<br />
Bard song (45?)
<br />
3 * Mage ward (50)
<br />

<br />
= 235pt DS. 
<br />

<br />
That's an affect that would get noticed. Even if the MT didn't have Bard song and clicked off our castable DS, he'd still have a 150pt one. 
<br />

<br />
Best case scenario would be an AE rampage boss and all in range have the stacked DSs. Now each AE will eat a noticable chunk off the boss. e.g. 30 ppl in ramp range = 30*235 = 7050 damage/rampage.
<br />

