				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>cannyar wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote"><span style="font-style: italic">whatever</span> doesn't fit in with "elements" either.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
I didn't spend a whole lot of time on what the effect for each element would be- especially since it would be mangled by the devs when they implemented it any way.  <img src="images/smiles/icon_razz.gif" alt="razz" border="0" /> 
<br />

<br />
generally i thought "What would be the effect of being surrounded or infused with this element" and got to
<br />

<br />
Water : cooling - refreshing - perhaps promoting healing and regeneration of health or mana.  Also possibly causing a diffration of vision making one protected by it harder to hit.   PR becuase of the rumored "immunity" to poison of the water elemental.
<br />

<br />
Air : swirling air around you - maing you harder to hit..
<br />

<br />
Earth : makes you tougher  - resist damage better or allows one to more forcefully parry blows ...
<br />

<br />
